headline: Dollar General Stock Joins Dollar Tree in the Green
summary: While retailers diverge over the impact of Trump's tariffs, some discount stores are seeing a boost. Dollar General shares jumped 3.9% Tuesday, while Dollar Tree shares gained 3.7%. That comes after Walmart said last week that it would raise prices on a range of goods over the next few months, citing the impact of tariffs.
